---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — ZeroTool"
  description="ZeroTool collects no personal data. All tools run client-side in your browser. Your data never leaves your device."
  lang="en"
>
  <div class="prose-container">
    <article class="prose">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="prose-meta">Last updated: April 2026</p>

      <h2>The Short Version</h2>
      <p>
        ZeroTool tools run entirely in your browser. We do not collect, store, or transmit any
        data you enter into our tools. Your data stays on your device.
      </p>

      <h2>Information We Do Not Collect</h2>
      <p>We do not collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Any input you provide to our tools (JSON, text, files, keys, passwords, etc.)</li>
        <li>Personal identification information</li>
        <li>Email addresses or account credentials (we have no accounts)</li>
        <li>Payment information</li>
        <li>Device identifiers tied to individuals</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We use Google Analytics 4 (GA4) to understand aggregate usage patterns — which tools
        are most popular, which pages are visited, and general geographic distribution. GA4 is
        configured with IP anonymization enabled, meaning the last octet of your IP address is
        masked before storage.
      </p>
      <p>
        GA4 sets session cookies for the duration of your visit. These are standard analytics
        cookies and do not identify you personally. You can opt out of GA4 tracking by using the
        <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Analytics opt-out browser add-on</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Browser Storage</h2>
      <p>
        ZeroTool stores a small amount of data in your browser's <code>localStorage</code> so
        the site stays usable across visits. None of it is ever transmitted to our servers.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Theme preference</strong> — light, dark, or system.</li>
        <li><strong>Recently used tools</strong> — the last 20 tool slugs you visited, used to
          power the "Recent" list.</li>
        <li><strong>Tool input &amp; preferences</strong> — for select tools (e.g. JSON Formatter,
          Base64, URL Encode), the most recent input is saved so you can refresh the page without
          losing work. Capped at 50 KB per tool and 2 MB total, with least-recently-used eviction.
          The <strong>JWT Decoder is exempt</strong> and never persists tokens. Click each tool's
          <em>Clear</em> button to wipe its saved input.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        No third-party advertising cookies are set. To clear everything, use your browser's
        "Clear site data" feature or DevTools → Application → Local Storage.
      </p>

      <h2>Tool Data</h2>
      <p>
        All computation performed by ZeroTool tools happens in your browser using JavaScript.
        Input data (strings, JSON, files) is processed locally and is never transmitted to our
        servers. We have no technical capability to access the data you process in our tools.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        We use the following third-party services:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> — anonymized usage analytics (described above)</li>
        <li><strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong> — hosting and CDN; Cloudflare may log request metadata per their own privacy policy</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        If we make material changes to this policy we will update the date at the top of this
        page. Continued use of ZeroTool after changes constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy? Email us at
        <a href="mailto:hello@zerotool.dev">hello@zerotool.dev</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
